- PASS (rare, to conserve mana)
  - Pass only if all non-redundant options are low-value/low-reliability this turn and saving mana clearly enables a higher-impact action next turn (e.g., big DAMAGE or crucial HEAL/DEFEND). Never pass if a reliable attack or needed survival action exists.

STRATEGY VS. COMBAT STYLE
- Weight ~60% on basic strategy, ~40% on \`combat_style\`.
- Style hints:
  - “Aggressive/burst/pressure/speed” ⇒ bias toward **DAMAGE** and non-redundant **BUFF** that increases offense. Likes high offensive_level
  - “Patient/control/precision/tempo” ⇒ bias toward **BUFF/DEBUFF/DEFEND**, then accurate **DAMAGE**. Biased against actions with lower accuracy
  - “Sustain/restore/growth” ⇒ more willing to **HEAL** at medium health_danger_level, likes to keep a high defensive_level
  - “Trickery/illusion” ⇒ favor **DEBUFF/BUFF** to tilt exchanges, then strike when enemy is weak.
